# Branch & Commit Rules

## Branch naming
Format: `<type>/<short-description-kebab>` (append issue/sprint if needed).

```
feat/library-scan
fix/transcode-session-leak
chore/ci-coverage-gate
docs/i18n-guide
```
- `main` is protected; no direct pushes, no force-pushes.
- Type set: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.

## Commit messages (Conventional Commits)
Format: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>` — English, imperative mood, lowercase, no period.

```
feat(library): add incremental scan with fs watcher
fix(auth): revoke refresh token on logout
test(streaming): cover transcode decision engine
```
- Small, focused commits. Subject line ≤ ~72 chars; explain the "why" in the body.

## DCO sign-off (required)
Every commit must be signed (no CLA, DCO only):

```bash
git commit -s -m "feat(metadata): add tmdb provider"
```
- `-s` adds the `Signed-off-by:` line. Unsigned commits are rejected in CI.

## General
- Do **not commit** secrets / `.env`-like credential files.
- No bypassing hooks (`--no-verify` etc.); do not modify `git config`.
